x4freetext: The U-120 cyclotron
The proton detectors, each made up of RCA 6655 A
photomultipliers and CsI(Tl), 0.08 cm thick crystals
were mounted of two of the four arms. The pulses from
one of the counters were amplified and then analysed on
S.A.I. 200-channel pulse amplitude analyser. The other
detector was fixed at 80 degrees, being used as a
supplementary monitor.
The gas target chamber was mounted in the centre of the
scattering chamber. It was formed by a 6 cm in diameter
and 6 cm high brass cylinder with two lateral windows
each being 1.2 cm high and having 145 degr. opening
covered by a 10 mu thickness aluminium foil. During the
experiments the neon pressure was maintained at 80 mm
Hg.
